& [PostApplyAcceptanceDesign] is the design contract for accepting applied workspace changes
  @ [apply_mutation_design] coordination/operator_approved_apply_mutation_design.sop
  @ [rollback_design] coordination/rollback_command_design.sop
  @ [created_at] 2026-05-29T17:08:00Z

  + [design_status] is ready_for_later_implementation
  + [authority_boundary] is acceptance_design_not_acceptance_runtime
  + [purpose] is prevent apply_result success from being mistaken for Manager/Shaliach final acceptance

  = must: require apply_result.sop
  = must: require verification_result.sop
  = must: require snapshot_materialization.sop
  = must: include rollback_result.sop when rollback occurred
  = must: require Manager final acceptance after apply verification passes
  = must: require Shaliach review when protocol scope, lineage, target paths, verification failure, rollback, or manual conflict resolution is present
  = must: mark acceptance blocked when verification fails
  = must: mark acceptance blocked when rollback_status is failed
  = must: record accepted_file_set and remaining_risk_set

  - never: treat apply_status applied as final acceptance by itself
  - never: hide rollback evidence from acceptance review
  - never: accept changes when Shaliach requires rework or pause

& [PostApplyAcceptanceRecord] is the future Manager-facing final acceptance artifact
  + [field] is acceptance_status
  + [field] is apply_result_ref
  + [field] is verification_result_ref
  + [field] is rollback_result_ref
  + [field] is manager_decision
  + [field] is shaliach_decision
  + [field] is accepted_file_set
  + [field] is remaining_risk_set
  + [field] is authority_boundary

& [ShaliachPostApplyReview] is the future protocol review gate
  + [trigger] is target paths expand beyond accepted packet scope
  + [trigger] is verification fails or is missing
  + [trigger] is rollback occurred
  + [trigger] is apply_result has partial writes or skipped files
  + [trigger] is Manager requests protocol counsel
  + [allowed_decision] is no_finding
  + [allowed_decision] is warning
  + [allowed_decision] is rework_required
  + [allowed_decision] is pause_required

& [ImplementationOrder] is the safe acceptance implementation path
  + [slice_1] is add PostApplyAcceptanceRecord and deterministic decision synthesis
  + [slice_2] is write acceptance record from apply_result and verification_result
  + [slice_3] is add Shaliach post-apply review conditions
  + [slice_4] is document operator workflow from apply through rollback through acceptance
  + [slice_5] is refresh spec audit and checkpoint
